The paper discusses modeling user behavior in online social media, which is a topic that can fall under several sub-categories. The most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Software Engineering), as the paper focuses on modeling user behavior and analyzing data from social media platforms. The sub-category cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely, as the paper discusses the impact of social media on user behavior. The sub-categories cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) are less likely but still possible, as the paper touches on topics related to social networks and user interface design.
